      "writtenOn": "2026-04-29T08:52:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, Redfish layer support is planned.\n\nYou\u0027re correct that service-config-manager provides per-instance service control. The firewall feature complements this by providing network-level traffic filtering that service-config-manager cannot.\n\nThe firewall can allow or block traffic based on:\n-IP addresses or subnets \n-Time windows \n-Protocol and port ranges \n-MAC addresses",
      "parentUuid": "32d39cb3_ee2460d2",
      "revId": "e8e6b143abe6d3e5ee82f0b4952b532558537aa0",
