      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T19:54:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Need a better problem description here.  You say people are manually setting up firewall rules, but don\u0027t enumerate WHY they\u0027re doing it.\n\n\u003e limiting BMC access to specific\nmanagement networks\n\nThis seems like a reasonable use case to support\n\n\u003e blocking unused protocols\n\nPlease look at the ManagerNetworkProtocol class in Redfish.  It implements runtime support for disabling unused protocols.\n\n\n\u003e implementing time-based access controls for maintenance windows.\n\nWould the \"time-based\" access generally be managed by a BMC?  Normally that would be managed by an external controller doing the update.",
      "revId": "e8e6b143abe6d3e5ee82f0b4952b532558537aa0",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
