    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "353c25c7_f5b795d8",
        "filename": "designs/firewall-configuration.md",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002754
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-16T07:11:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ManagerNetworkProtocol and firewall serve different purposes:\nManagerNetworkProtocol: Disables services globally (e.g., \"turn off SSH completely\")\nFirewall: Controls network access per source (e.g., \"allow SSH only from specific IP\" or \"block all UDP from specific IPs\")\nThey\u0027re complementary - one controls which services run, the other controls who can access them. That said, IP-based filtering is the primary use case.\n\nThe implementation supports time-based rules (using iptables\u0027 time module) for scenarios where rules should automatically activate/deactivate at specific times without external intervention.",
      "parentUuid": "6fe1156e_6cc45557",
      "revId": "e8e6b143abe6d3e5ee82f0b4952b532558537aa0",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
