      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T19:54:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please rewrite as actual use cases.  \"reorder (all) firewall rules\" is overly broad and not generally how we organize dbus.  Also, how (at a requirements level) do you expect users to use these if they\u0027re only exposed to DBus?  Only on dbus would mean that we\u0027re still just executing shell scripts, at which point, we haven\u0027t really replaced nftables commands, right?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 63,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "e8e6b143abe6d3e5ee82f0b4952b532558537aa0",
