      "writtenOn": "2026-06-16T07:11:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is input filtering for traffic destined to the BMC itself, not port forwarding/NAT.\nThese are standard iptables -A INPUT rules with -p tcp --dport \u003cport\u003e or --dport \u003cstart\u003e:\u003cend\u003e for ranges. The filtering happens on traffic coming into the BMC, before it reaches the listening services.",
